commit.message:
Fix example and segfault when adding a value to an empty document

Fixes the example and makes it clearer how to compile it.

Also fixes the segfault when adding a value to an empty document. If
`children().empty()` is true, `children().front()` segfaults because
there's nothing for it to return a ref to. Rework logic so we only
attempt to check the first element if we know it exists.

Fixes #130.

Fixes the example and makes it clearer how to compile it.

Also fixes the segfault when adding a value to an empty document. If
`children().empty()` is true, `children().front()` segfaults because
there's nothing for it to return a ref to. Rework logic so we only
attempt to check the first element if we know it exists.

Fixes #130.

commit.message:
(maint) System Locales fails regex backup

In case the locales on the system fails(due to gconv, or somethingelse),
leatherman will use boost::format and boost::regex, to create %N%style
formatting. 'regex' is only included in CMakeLists.txt if localesare
enabled, but if they fail, 'regex' will be required

This PR adds 'regex' to BOOST_COMPONENTS even if leatherman useslocales,
as an extra check in case the locales are enabled but fail.

(maint) Fix docs links, update Doxyfile, expand README

Adds a short section to the README on how to use the library.

Fixes documentation links that used camel-case references (so they
didn't match the class names). Upgrades the Doxyfile format for a newer
version of Doxygen.
